gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 115, Warriors 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers defeated the Warriors, 115-104 tonight in Cleveland. Donovan Mitchell contributed a team-high 31 points (5 3PT FG) to go with seven assists, and two rebounds, with Darius Garland adding an additional 24 points and seven assists in the game. Stephen Curry finished with a team-high 28 points (7 3PT FG) for the Warriors as Draymond Green added 18 points, eight assists, and three rebounds. The Cavaliers improve their record to 3-4 with the win, while the Warriors move to 5-2 for the season.
